INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'cdcdbfee-e502-431b-b8a9-b9ee0b962df0',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Helm Health Checks — Wiring Liveness, Readiness, and Startup Probes in Your Chart$escape$,
  $escape$Helm doesn't abstract Kubernetes probes — it just templates them. The power is in parameterizing probe configs so operators can tune them per-environment without forking your chart.

All three probes live under `spec.containers[].livenessProbe`, `readinessProbe`, and `startupProbe` in your Deployment template. A common pattern is to expose them as `values.yaml` keys: `livenessProbe`, `readinessProbe`, `startupProbe` — each an object that gets injected verbatim using `toYaml | nindent`. This lets users override the entire probe block without touching the template.

Use `startupProbe` for slow-starting containers (JVMs, model-loading services) — it gates the other two until the app is up. Set `failureThreshold * periodSeconds` to your worst-case cold-start budget. Once it passes, `livenessProbe` takes over to restart deadlocked pods and `readinessProbe` controls Service endpoint membership.

Avoid hardcoding `initialDelaySeconds` in the template — it's a smell. Prefer `startupProbe` with a generous threshold and zero `initialDelaySeconds` on liveness/readiness. Expose `livenessProbe.httpGet.path` and port as separate values so the chart works across apps with different health endpoints.$escape$,
  $escape$# values.yaml
startupProbe:
  httpGet:
    path: /healthz
    port: http
  failureThreshold: 30
  periodSeconds: 10

livenessProbe:
  httpGet:
    path: /healthz
    port: http
  periodSeconds: 15
  failureThreshold: 3

readinessProbe:
  httpGet:
    path: /ready
    port: http
  periodSeconds: 10
  failureThreshold: 3

# templates/deployment.yaml (inside containers block)
{{- with .Values.startupProbe }}
startupProbe: {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}
{{- end }}
{{- with .Values.livenessProbe }}
livenessProbe: {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}
{{- end }}
{{- with .Values.readinessProbe }}
readinessProbe: {{- toYaml . | nindent 12 }}
{{- end }}$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
